S. Korea’s Bahk Urges Contingency Planning for Global Shocks

-- B y   E u n k y u n g   S e o
-- 
2011-06-24T07:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/s-korea-s-bahk-urges-contingency-planning-for-global-shocks.html
South Korea ’s Finance Minister Bahk
Jae Wan urged contingency planning for potential external shocks
as uncertainty rises about a global economic recovery.  Potential risks to South Korea’s economy include an end to
the U.S. quantitative easing program, a possible tightening in
 China  and volatile commodity prices, as well as the European
debt crisis, Bahk said at a government meeting in  Seoul .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Eunkyung Seo in Seoul at 
 eseo3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
